Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @black sesame seeds{5%grams} and half the @Chinese five spice{1/2%sachet}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways.

Pop the @British chicken thighs{4} onto one side of another large baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the remaining @Chinese five spice{1/2%sachet}, then rub to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

When the potatoes have ~{15%minutes} remaining, roast the chicken on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through and tender, ~{16-18%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the chicken has ~{10%minutes} remaining, remove the tray from the oven.

Pop the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%grams} alongside the chicken. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

Return the tray to the middle shelf of your oven for the remaining time, until the broccoli is tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain any fat from the chicken tray, then drizzle the @hoisin sauce{60%grams} over the chicken thighs and turn to coat.

Share the hoisin chicken thighs between your plates. Serve the roasted potatoes and broccoli alongside. Add a dollop of @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} for dipping. Enjoy!